Assignment 6

TX

g1<-ggplot() + geom_sf(data=map_vote %>% filter(state=='Texas'),aes(fill = rate))+
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-108, -92), ylim = c(25, 38), expand = T)+
  facet_wrap(~year, ncol =1)+
  labs(fill = 'democrat vote rate')

g2<-ggplot() + geom_sf(data=map_unemp %>% filter(state=='TX'),aes(fill = rate))+
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-108, -92), ylim = c(25, 38), expand = T)+
  facet_wrap(~year, ncol =1)+
  labs(fill = 'unemployment rate')

grid.arrange(g1,g2, ncol=2, top = 'Democrat Voting Rate and Unemplotment rate in Taxes')

The unemployment rate is decreasing in year. The conties have higher democrat rate have lower employment rate except northwest
